parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tread Separation and Blowout of Powerking Towmax Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation and blowout of Powerking Towmax tires can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle and trailer.
symptoms: often occurring at high speeds (around 60 mph).

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Bumper Failure on Keystone Cougar Trailers
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear bumper failure can cause the bumper to fall off, creating a hazard on the road and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Rear bumper separating from the RV frame

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power King Tow Max Tire Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the Power King Tow Max tires can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the trailer, potentially leading to serious injuries or fatalities.

The sudden and catastrophic failure of the spare tire can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle and surrounding structures, posing a significant risk to the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The spare tire blows out suddenly
and a large hole remains in the carcass with jagged steel belt cords protruding
causing damage to the vehicle and surrounding structures.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure due to Manufacturing Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tires with manufacturing defects can fail suddenly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle and surrounding structures, posing a significant risk to the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: and a large hole remains in the carcass with jagged steel belt cords protruding
causing damage to the vehicle and surrounding structures.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Metal Fatigue Failure of Slide-Out Bumper/Bike Rack Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the slide-out bumper/bike rack assembly can cause the spare tire and attached items to detach while driving, creating a hazardous road debris situation that can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The bumper holding the spare tire and bike rack begins to sag or hang loose
the assembly fails to retract properly
the metal components show signs of fatigue or cracking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the furnace fuel line can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, or asphyxiation due to fuel vapors accumulating in the living area, underbelly, and storage areas of the RV.
symptoms: fuel vapors in the living area
crushed or cracked copper fuel lines
fuel line damage due to improper installation or routing over the frame and under the floor.
